```

This setup will create a Discord bot that can ban users when the `/ban` slash command is used. Make sure you have the appropriate permissions to ban members in the server where you're running this bot.

Certainly! To convert Markdown formatted text into HTML, you can use a library like `pandocfilters` or `libsoup`, but these libraries might be overkill for simple cases. A more straightforward approach is to use a third-party library like `markdown` (part of the `commonmark` library in C++).

Here's an example of how you can write a C++ function to convert Markdown to HTML using the `commonmark` library:

First, ensure you have the necessary library installed. On many Linux systems, you can install it via:

```sh
sudo apt-get install libcommonmark-dev
```

